headline: Truist upgrades Oshkosh saying stock ‘too cheap to ignore’
summary: Investing.com -- Truist upgraded Oshkosh (NYSE:OSK) Corp to Buy from Hold and raised its price target to $127 from $93, citing a compelling valuation, strong backlog in the vocational segment, and trough-level defense margins poised to recover.

headline: U.S. Banks' Brokered Deposits Decline For 5th Consecutive Quarter In Q1
summary: Brokered deposits at US banks declined for the fifth quarter in a row as many banks reduce reliance on expensive sources of funding amid the growth of low-cost deposits.
